THE owner of a private game reserve near Thabazimbi in Limpopo is in hospital after being mauled by one of hislions. Limpopo police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the incident happened on Monday. Ngoepe said the man sustained injuries to his neck and jaw. “He was immediately taken to hospital with serious injuries. “He is recovering from his wounds,” he said. In a short video clip, the man is seen walking behind the lion in a den. The man then turns his back on the lion and it quickly spots him and chases him as he runs for a metal gate. The lion then drags him into nearby bushes where the man lies motionless. A witness can be heard screaming: “Somebody help, please! Oh my God!” A couple of gunshots can also be heard in the background. Attempts to contact the game reserve were unsuccessful. – NEWS24